The paper deals with wireless networks and their capacity scaling, which are topics typically covered in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of multiple antennas and beamforming also suggests the sub-category of Signal Processing (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of TDMA and hierarchical cooperation, which are related to the sub-categories of Multimedia (cs.MM) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DS).
